The paper proposes a pre-training method for learning question representations in the education domain, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves learning from unlabeled data, which suggests the possibility of using unsupervised learning techniques, such as clustering and dimensionality reduction, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of images and side information in test questions, which suggests the possibility of using computer vision techniques, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Deep Learning).
